Resource Local JTA (Java Transaction API) Scope Single database Multiple databases / resources Who manages Application code or Spring Application server / container Transaction type in persistence.xml <code>RESOURCE_LOCAL</code> <code>JTA</code> EntityManager creation <code>emf.createEntityManager()</code> Container injects it Commit <code>em.getTransaction().commit()</code> <code>UserTransaction.commit()</code> Use case Most Spring Boot apps (single DB) Distributed systems, multiple DBs, JMS + DB <p>Resource Local example (manual)</p> <pre><code>EntityManager em = emf.createEntityManager();
em.getTransaction().begin();

em.persist(new Employee("Alice"));

em.getTransaction().commit();  // commits to single DB
em.close();
</code></pre> <p>JTA example (container-managed)</p> <pre><code>@Stateless  // EJB or Jakarta EE
public class EmployeeService {

    @PersistenceContext
    private EntityManager em;  // container provides this

    public void transfer() {
        // operations on Database A
        em.persist(new Employee("Alice"));

        // operations on Database B (different persistence unit)
        // ...

        // container commits BOTH databases atomically using JTA
    }
}
</code></pre>
